						               													<description>Fire Team: Normandie 44 is an hex and counter boardgame convertible to miniatures wargame.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It covers tactical combat in Normandy after the landing of June 6, during WW2.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scale&amp;#10;25 mm hex = 5 meters, &amp;#10;1 counter = 1 to 3 Soldiers&amp;#10;1 Turn = ~1 minute&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Principle of the Game: &amp;#10;teams are part of a Combat Group (Squad).&amp;#10;The Squad Leader gives an Action Order - Player's choice - for the current Game Turn. &amp;#10;These Action Orders are semi-simultaneous for the 2 players in the Game Turn:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Fire, &amp;#10;     Crawl, &amp;#10;     Run,&amp;#10;     Jump,&amp;#10;     Take Cover...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Make a choice: &amp;#10;take a Shot? Move ? get in cover? spot the enemy, before he spots you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the pdf download, you will find :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Rules of the Game covering Infantry and&amp;#10;     Tables for:&amp;#10;         movements,&amp;#10;         Fire,&amp;#10;         Moral, etc.   &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;     Specific rules for Terrains types in Normandy.&amp;#10;     3 Scenarios &amp;#10;     Counters (US and Heer), &amp;#10;     Formations Cards and &amp;#10;     Markers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;No map is included in this pdf.&amp;#10;You will find game boards for the game on Wargame Vault.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Rules are organized in chapters, &amp;#10;included in the core rules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Chapter A - Infantry Base&amp;#10;     Chapter B - Normandy Terrains. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;in the expansions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Chapter C - Artillery and Air Support&amp;#10;     Chapter D - Vehicles and Tanks &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
